xtended length of time, as it will draw moisture from the air and become sticky. Although best eaten soon after it is made, it can be stored in a bag, or wrapped in cling film and stored in airtight containers, for up to <b>1 week.<b> Dipping honeycomb in chocolate will help extend the shelf-life by a few days."],"basicInfo":["medium","10m","1h 30m","1"]}